    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "A 1968 federal law banning mail‑order real‑estate sales forced Schwartz and partner Al Tarrson to stop the practice.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        25
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Villages%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "By the early 1990s the Villages boasted more than 8,000 residents, three golf courses, and a Winn‑Dixie supermarket.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
